==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Pentose
<hw>Pen"tose</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[<ets>Penta-</ets> +
<ets>-ose</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Chem.)</fld> <def>Any of a group of sugars
of the formula <chform>C5H10O5</chform>, such as as
<stype>arabinose</stype> or <stype>ribose</stype>; -- so called from the
five carbon atoms in the molecule. They are not fermented by
yeast.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Pentoxide</ent>⟦br⟧
